🎓 Student Performance Prediction System
A machine learning web application that predicts student exam marks and mental wellness based on cognitive and behavioral factors.

🔗 Live Demo
https://student-performance-garima.streamlit.app/

📌 Features
🔮 Marks Prediction — Predicts exam percentage based on study habits & cognitive inputs
🧠 Mental Wellness Analysis — Scores mental health (0–100) based on stress, sleep & motivation
💡 Personalized Suggestions — Actionable mental health tips based on student inputs
📊 Performance Factor Chart — Visual breakdown of all contributing factors
🔍 Feature Importance Chart — Shows which factors impact marks the most
🏆 Grade Prediction — A+ to D grading system
🔬 Model Comparison — 3 models compared, best one selected automatically
🧠 ML Model Comparison
Model	R² Score	MAE
Linear Regression	0.7728	4.98
Random Forest	0.7869	4.53
Gradient Boosting ✅	0.8259	4.18
Gradient Boosting was selected as the final model for best accuracy.

📊 Input Features
Feature	Type
Study Hours	Academic
Attendance %	Academic
Sleep Hours	Cognitive
Stress Level	Cognitive
Focus Level	Cognitive
Motivation Level	Cognitive
Social Media Usage	Behavioral
Revision Frequency	Academic
Concentration Level	Cognitive
Class Attention	Academic
🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend: Streamlit
ML Models: Scikit-learn (Linear Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting)
Data: NumPy, Pandas
Visualization: Matplotlib
Model Persistence: Joblib
📁 Project Structure
student-performance-predictor/
├── app.py                  # Main Streamlit application
├── train_model.py          # Model training & comparison
├── generate_data.py        # Synthetic dataset generation
├── student_data.csv        # Generated dataset (1000 records)
├── student_model.pkl       # Saved best model (Gradient Boosting)
├── model_results.csv       # Model comparison results
├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies
└── README.md
▶️ Run Locally
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/student-performance-predictor.git
cd student-performance-predictor

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Generate data (optional - already included)
python generate_data.py

# Train models
python train_model.py

# Run app
streamlit run app.py
📝 About the Dataset
Dataset is synthetically generated using realistic distributions based on educational psychology research patterns. Real student data was avoided due to student privacy concerns. The dataset contains 1000 student records with 10 features each.

